{{update|date=March 2018}} [[File:Green Day At Bråvalla Festival In Sweden By Daniel Åhs Karlsson.jpg|thumb|right| [[Billie Joe Armstrong]] and [[Green Day]] at the Bråvalla festival in 2013]] [[File:Rammstein At Bråvalla Festival In Sweden By Daniel Åhs Karlsson.jpg|thumb|right|[[Rammstein]] at the festival in 2013]]
'''Bråvalla Festival''' was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] four-day music festival that was held annually. It was Sweden's biggest and most popular music festival. It was held at [[Bråvalla flygflottilj]] outside of [[Norrköping]]. The inaugural season of the festival was from 27 to 29 June 2013. It headlined [[Rammstein]], [[Green Day]] and [[Avicii]] in additions to tens of artists and acts. The second season was held between the 26 June and 28 June 2014 and was headlined by [[Iron Maiden]], [[Kanye West]] and [[Kings of Leon]]. The third season of the festival was held between 25–27 June in 2015. It was headlined by [[Robbie Williams]], [[Muse (band)|Muse]] and [[Calvin Harris]]. The fourth season was held between 30 June – 2 July in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.nt.se/kultur-noje/bravalla-festival/maggio-slar-bravalla-rekord-9921358.aspx |title=Maggio slår Bråvalla-rekord - Bråvalla Festival - Norrköpings Tidningar |publisher=Nt.se |date=2014-06-09 |accessdate=2014-06-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upplev.norrkoping.se/Br%E5valla+Festival_1__1053.html |title=Bråvalla festival 2014 - Upplev Norrköping |publisher=Upplev.norrkoping.se |date= |accessdate=2014-06-27 |df= }}{{dead link|date=January 2017|bot=medic}}</ref>
The hosts, FKP Scorpio, estimated about 40,000 people would attend the festival in 2013 but eventually 51,590 tickets were sold.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.nt.se/nyheter/artikel.aspx?articleid=8653499/ |title=Nyheter - Norrköpings Tidningar |publisher=Nt.se |date= |accessdate=2014-06-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212014944/http://www.nt.se/nyheter/artikel.aspx?articleid=8653499%2F |archivedate=2013-12-12 |df= }}</ref> This record was again broken in 2014 when 51,683 tickets were sold.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/musik/rockbjornen/article19104218.ab |title=Bråvalla slår publikrekord igen &#124; Rockbjörnen &#124; Musik &#124; Nöjesbladet &#124; Aftonbladet |publisher=Aftonbladet.se |date=2014-06-23 |accessdate=2014-06-27}}</ref><ref name="thelocal1">{{cite web|url=http://www.thelocal.se/20140627/lightning-strikes-music-festival |title=Lightning strikes Bråvalla music festival - The Local |publisher=Thelocal.se |date= |accessdate=2014-06-27}}</ref>
On 27 June 2014, several people were injured during the festival when lightning struck and one person was taken to hospital with life-threatening injuries.<ref name="thelocal1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goteborgdaily.se/festival-goer-critical-after-lightning-strike |title=Festival-goer 'critical' after lightning strike - Göteborg Daily |publisher=Goteborgdaily.se |date= |accessdate=2014-06-27 |deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140701051201/http://www.goteborgdaily.se/festival-goer-critical-after-lightning-strike |archivedate=2014-07-01 |df= }}</ref>
On July 1, 2017 FKP Scorpio announced that Bråvalla will not take place in 2018 due to a number of sexual assaults.<ref>{{cite news |author= |title=Bråvalla ställs in nästa år efter anmälda sexbrott |url=https://www.svd.se/bravallafestivalen-stalls-in-nasta-ar |newspaper=[[Svenska dagbladet]] |id= |date=1 July 2017 |page= |accessdate=1 July 2017 |language= |arkivurl= |arkivdatum= }}</ref>
